  "body": "Docker automatically brings up `lo`, but in the rkt case kubelet creates the loopback interface. When using kubenet, it's brought \"UP\" by kubenet itself now, but with CNI it isn't.\n\nI think we need to do one of the following:\n- Add special casing in CNI to call the loopback plugin always (matches what kubenet does)\n- Special case calling CNI twice, once always with loopback, once with the configured CNI plugin in the rkt code (special cased for all non-kubenet non-no-op plugins)\n\ncc @kubernetes/sig-rktnetes \n",
